Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom, has commiserated with his Kogi State counterpart, Governor Yahaya Bello over the loss of his mother, Hajia Hauwau Oziohu Bello. In a statement by his spokesman, Terver Akase, Ortom said the death of a loved one such as mother can be devastating and quite painful. The Governor encouraged Governor Bello to take solace in the fact that his beloved mother lived a fulfilled life and has gone to rest with the Lord. He also sympathized with the entire Bello Ipemida Ochi family and prayed that God grants their matriarch eternal rest.